 [\"Q41176\", \"Q40357\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Prison_Holloway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HM_Prison_Holloway\"}, {\"begin\": 3081, \"end\": 3095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Roberts_(fighter)\", \"score\": 0.9171939871993402, \"rank\": 0.050154320987637786, \"text\": \"Daniel Roberts\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Roberts_(fighter)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Roberts_(fighter)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Roberts out-leaned Rasheed Broadbell of Jamaica, who finished with bronze    Setting the world record in the women's 400-meter hurdle wasn't enough forSydney McLaughlin-Levroneon Thursday.\", \"from\": 3116, \"to\": 3304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3156, \"end\": 3163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999953765561729, \"rank\": 4.623465002787113e-06, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She wishes her record-breaking 50.37 time was lower.\", \"from\": 3305, \"to\": 3357, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Yeah, I mean, across the line I was definitely grateful for that time, I was hoping it was a little faster, but like I said, I am sure there is some things in the middle there we can clean up,\\\" she told reporters after the race.\", \"from\": 3359, \"to\": 3588, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier this summer, she lowered the 400 hurdles world record for the fifth time since June 2021.\", \"from\": 3590, \"to\": 3687, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She previously won gold at the Tokyo Olympics in 2021, where she set the world record with a 50.65.\", \"from\": 3688, \"to\": 3787, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. men's basketball team faced a double-digit deficit for most of its semifinal game against Serbia, but a fourth quarter comeback led by Steph Curry, LeBron James, Kevin Durant and Joel Embiid stunned Nikola Jokic and company as the U.S. won 95-91.\", \"from\": 3789, \"to\": 4044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3888, \"end\": 3894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999845224035185, \"rank\": 1.5477835257446986e-05, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3933, \"end\": 3944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steph Curry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\"}, {\"begin\": 3946, \"end\": 3958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LeBron James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 3966, \"end\": 3972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.910120967670877e-21, \"text\": \"Durant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\"}, {\"begin\": 3977, \"end\": 3988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Joel Embiid\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Curry led all scorers with 36 points, including two big free throws to seal the win in the final seconds.\", \"from\": 4046, \"to\": 4151, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"James notched his second triple-double of his Olympic career with 16 points, 12 rebounds and 10 assists.\", \"from\": 4152, \"to\": 4256, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4152, \"end\": 4157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.938292155412822e-16, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Serbia was led by Bogan Bogdanovic who scored 20 points, while Jokic had 17 points and 11 assists.\", \"from\": 4258, \"to\": 4356, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4258, \"end\": 4264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999845224035185, \"rank\": 1.5477835257446986e-05, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4276, \"end\": 4281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bogan_River\", \"score\": 0.7832988824582379, \"rank\": 0.27665189159906467, \"text\": \"Bogan\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bogan_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bogan_River\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Serbia went into the fourth quarter with a 76-63 lead, but could not hold off an avalanche of scoring and defensive plays by the U.S. in the closing minutes.\", \"from\": 4358, \"to\": 4515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4358, \"end\": 4364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999845224035185, \"rank\": 1.5477835257446986e-05, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. trailed by as much as 17 points in the first half.\", \"from\": 4516, \"to\": 4575, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. previously defeated Serbia in group play 110-84.\", \"from\": 4577, \"to\": 4634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4606, \"end\": 4612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999845224035185, \"rank\": 1.5477835257446986e-05, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone has gotten into the habit of breaking world records.\", \"from\": 4636, \"to\": 4714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4636, \"end\": 4642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999995905628495, \"rank\": 4.0943626547372445e-07, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 25-year-old track star did just that in the women's 400-meter hurdles final on Thursday to win gold and successfully defend herOlympic title.McLaughlin-Levrone set a new world record with an official time of 50.37 seconds, becoming just the first woman in Olympics history to win gold in that event twice.\", \"from\": 4716, \"to\": 5025, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"McLaughlin-Levrone has set that record six times, most recently breaking the record at the U.S. Olympic trials in June.\", \"from\": 5027, \"to\": 5146, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA teammate Anna Cockrell ran a personal best of 51.87 to win the silver medal.\", \"from\": 5148, \"to\": 5233, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5148, \"end\": 5156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/U