/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles appeared to call over for medical attention immediately after crossing the finish line, although it wasn't immediately clear if he had sustained an injury.\", \"from\": 6031, \"to\": 6192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia's Michelle Jenneke tripped and fell during the women's 100-meter hurdles event at theParis Olympicson Wednesday.\", \"from\": 6196, \"to\": 6318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6196, \"end\": 6205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9999988437036654, \"rank\": 7.488065822467799e-07, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 6208, \"end\": 6216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"score\": 0.9999917445643107, \"rank\": 8.254769039541276e-06, \"text\": \"Michelle\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jenneke appeared to have an issue with the third hurdle on the track at Stade de France.\", \"from\": 6320, \"to\": 6408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6392, \"end\": 6407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 6392, \"end\": 6407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tumble ultimately caused her to finish in last place in the heat.\", \"from\": 6409, \"to\": 6478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She did finish the event, which left her hopes of qualifying for the semifinals alive.\", \"from\": 6479, \"to\": 6565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jenneke had a shot at redemption in a repechage, which effectively grants competitors a second chance, on Thursday but crossed the finish line last, ending her Olympic journey.\", \"from\": 6567, \"to\": 6743, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chantz Martin contributed to this report.\", \"from\": 6745, \"to\": 6786, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6752, \"end\": 6758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"score\": 0.9999999554074758, \"rank\": 4.45928782441259e-08, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States women's volleyball team is one win away from successfully defending their title at the2024 Paris Olympicsafter they defeated Brazil in three sets during Thursday's semifinal match.\", \"from\": 6790, \"to\": 6988, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6794, \"end\": 6807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.035305574085896e-13, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 6933, \"end\": 6939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8361122518013722, \"rank\": 0.1960116572245212, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S., who won gold in Tokyo in 2021 after a win over Brazil in the finals, took the first and third set before Brazil kept their gold medal chances alive in the fourth with a 25-23 victory.\", \"from\": 6990, \"to\": 7183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7016, \"end\": 7021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999913526981878, \"rank\": 8.647376246923176e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 7047, \"end\": 7053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8361122518013722, \"rank\": 0.1960116572245212, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 7105, \"end\": 7111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8361122518013722, \"rank\": 0.1960116572245212, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Americans would seal their fate in the fifth set with a 15-11 win to close out the nearly two-hour long semifinal.\", \"from\": 7185, \"to\": 7307, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Another gold medal in Paris would mark just the second Olympic title for the women's volleyball team.\", \"from\": 7309, \"to\": 7410, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7331, \"end\": 7336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0214308004096505e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French runner Alice Finot may not have come away with a medal from the Paris Olympic Games, but she didcome away with a fianc\\u00e9.\", \"from\": 7412, \"to\": 7539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7412, \"end\": 7418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9996897553963994, \"rank\": 0.0002925913109676425, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 7426, \"end\": 7431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portrayals_of_Alice_in_Wonderland\", \"score\": 0.9814615070212434, \"rank\": 0.01888866027487107, \"text\": \"Alice\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portrayals_of_Alice_in_Wonderland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portrayals_of_Alice_in_Wonderland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finot finished fourth in the women's steeplechase race, running it in a time of 8:58.67.\", \"from\": 7541, \"to\": 7629, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the race she found her boyfriend, Spanish triathlete Bruno Martinez, and attached a \\\"Love is in Paris\\\" pin on his shirt and proposed with the Olympic pin.\", \"from\": 7630, \"to\": 7790, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7732, \"end\": 7737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0214308004096505e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I told myself that if I ran under nine minutes, knowing that nine is my lucky number and that we have been together for nine years, then I would propose,\\\" Finot said.\", \"from\": 7792, \"to\": 7959, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not like doing things like everyone else.\", \"from\": 7960, \"to\": 8007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Since he had not done it yet, I thought maybe it was up to me.\\\"\", \"from\": 8008, \"to\": 8071, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris is the city of love, after all.\", \"from\": 8073, \"to\": 8110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8073, \"end\": 8078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0214308004096505e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ryan Canfield contributed to this report.\", \"from\": 8112, \"to\": 8153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8112, \"end\": 8116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 2.216392100181983e-12, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}, {\"begin\": 8117, \"end\": 8125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haldimand_County\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.953353703550992e-18, \"text\": \"Canfield\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haldimand_County\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haldimand_County\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The most decorated woman in American Olympics history will add one more thing to her resume: a flag bearer at the closing ceremony at the2024 Paris Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 8155, \"to\": 8317, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8183, \"end\": 8191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999985652604043, \"rank\": 1.4344359790087024e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Katie Ledecky received a call from fellow Team USA swimmer Bobby Finke, who delivered her the news.\", \"from\": 8319, \"to\": 8418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8319, \"end\": 8332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}, {\"begin\": 8361, \"end\": 8369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9961931538759121, \"rank\": 0.003821393581607948, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 8378, \"end\": 8389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bobby Finke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just wanted to thank you, you have been a huge inspiration and a leader to us for 12 years.\\\"\", \"from\": 8420, \"to\": 8515, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Finke said.\", \"from\": 8516, \"to\": 8527, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have gotten know you for these 12 years, and I really can not think of anyone better to lead us out of these Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 8528, \"to\": 8654, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So, you are going to need a new jacket.\\\"\", \"from\": 8655, \"to\": 8695, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky was honored to be selected.\", \"from\": 8697, \"to\": 8732, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Thank you!\", \"from\": 8734, \"to\": 8745, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thank you, Team USA.\", \"from\": 8746, \"to\": 8766, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is a huge honor.\", \"from\": 8767, \"to\": 8788, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Can not wait for closing ceremonies and it's been an honor representing our country here in Paris and I am so proud to be a part of this team.\\\"\", \"from\": 8789, \"to\": 8932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8881, \"end\": 8886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0214308004096505e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky is taking home four medals in these Summer Games.\", \"from\": 8934, \"to\": 8991, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She won bronze in the women's 400m freestyle, silver in the women's 4x200m freestyle, her fourth consecutive gold medal in the 800m freestyle, and set an Olympic record winning gold in the women's 1500m freestyle.\", \"from\": 8992, \"to\": 9205, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ryan Canfield contributed to this report.\", \"from\": 9207, \"to\": 9248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9207, \"end\": 9211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 2.216392100181983e-12, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}, {\"begin\": 9212, \"end\": 9220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haldimand_County\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.953353703550992e-18, \"text\": \"Canfield\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haldimand_County\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haldimand_County\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sam Watson saved his best for last on Thursday in the men's speed climbing final.\", \"from\": 9252, \"to\": 9333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9252, \"end\": 9262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\", \"score\": 0.8551999212396617, \"rank\": 0.16931216931219462, \"text\": \"Sam Watson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The American set a world record for the second time in theParis Gameswith a time of 4.74 seconds in the bronze medal match.\", \"from\": 9335, \"to\": 9458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9339, \"end\": 9347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999985652604043, \"rank\": 1.4344359790087024e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 18-year-old previously set the world record with a time of 4.75 seconds in an elimination heat earlier in the week, breaking his own world record of 4.79 seconds that he set in April.\", \"from\": 9459, \"to\": 9646, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After that heat, he lost in the semifinals to Wu Peng of China.\", \"from\": 9648, \"to\": 9711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9694, \"end\": 9701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wu_Peng\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0749716456426609e-27, \"text\": \"Wu Peng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wu_Peng\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wu_Peng\"}, {\"begin\": 9705, \"end\": 9710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9735023017053525, \"rank\": 0.0272156290849941, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Watson came in as the heavy favorite for gold.\", \"from\": 9712, \"to\": 9758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9712, \"end\": 9718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dr._Watson\", \"score\": 0.9065085002573117, \"rank\": 0.10313178847210305, \"text\": \"Watson\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dr._Watson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dr._Watson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While he did not secure the top of the podium, he will still walk away with a world record and a bronze medal from the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 9759, \"to\": 9890, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Leonardo Veddriq of Indonesia won the gold with a time of 4.75 seconds in the final, narrowly edging out Peng, who finished with 4.77.\", \"from\": 9892, \"to\": 10026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9892, \"end\": 9900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 0.9999985628302379, \"rank\": 1.4371722283616649e-06, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 9912, \"end\": 9921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia_national_badminton_team\", \"score\": 0.9996108404943174, \"rank\": 0.0003888879566769431, \"text\": \"Indonesia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia_national_badminton_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia_national_badminton_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ryan Canfield contributed to this report.\", \"from\": 10028, \"to\": 10069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10028, \"end\": 10032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 2.216392100181983e-12, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nol