\": 10859, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET    More than two years after missing out on gold medals due to an\\u00a0opponent's doping use, theU.S.\", \"from\": 10860, \"to\": 10959, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic figure skating teamfinally received their hardware.\", \"from\": 10960, \"to\": 11019, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. and Japan figure skaters took to a podium at Champions Park in Paris on Wednesday to receive their gold and silver medals, which they earned at the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics.\", \"from\": 11021, \"to\": 11203, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11030, \"end\": 11035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9996306792554223, \"rank\": 0.00034666736141135483, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 11089, \"end\": 11094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0214308004096505e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the time, Russia took gold in the event, much due to the help of 15-year-oldKamila Valieva,who became the first woman ever to land a quadruple jump at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 11204, \"to\": 11371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11217, \"end\": 11223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999525070973, \"rank\": 4.6640328040243804e-08, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Valieva tested positive for trimetazidine - a banned drug that prevents angina - at the Russian national championships in December 2021, and the results of the test were only made public the day after the team final in Beijing.\", \"from\": 11373, \"to\": 11609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11470, \"end\": 11500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Figure_Skating_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.138135023169711e-14, \"text\": \"Russian national championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Figure_Skating_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Figure_Skating_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 11601, \"end\": 11608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.748522323779218e-25, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee (IOC) then ruled that no medals for the team figure skating event would be officially presented until Valieva's case was resolved.\", \"from\": 11610, \"to\": 11776, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11614, \"end\": 11651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympians then had to wait nearly two years to know what medal they would even receive.\", \"from\": 11778, \"to\": 11869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11778, \"end\": 11791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daptone_Records\", \"score\": 0.9999999950750862, \"rank\": 4.925152000791541e-09, \"text\": \"The Olympians\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"h